Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.31,0:00:09.38,720PCNUP,,0,0,0,,这个YouTuber把重型猎鹰Falcon Heavy说成Falcon 9 Heavy 你们知道是啥就行
Dialogue: 1,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.31,720PCN,,0,0,0,,2018年2月6日
Dialogue: 2,0:00:00.00,0:00:03.31,720PEN,,0,0,0,,A few days ago on the 6th of February 2018
Dialogue: 1,0:00:03.31,0:00:09.38,720PCN,,0,0,0,,SpaceX的重型猎鹰火箭首飞
Dialogue: 2,0:00:03.31,0:00:09.38,720PEN,,0,0,0,,SpaceX's first test launch of the Falcon 9 heavy the most powerful rocket since
Dialogue: 1,0:00:09.38,0:00:14.88,720PCN,,0,0,0,,成为土星五号、能源号以来成功发射的推力最大的火箭，载荷是马一龙的红色
Dialogue: 2,0:00:09.38,0:00:14.88,720PEN,,0,0,0,,the Saturn 5 successfully launched a payload of Elon Musk's own cherry red
Dialogue: 1,0:00:14.88,0:00:20.82,720PCN,,0,0,0,,特斯拉跑车，上面有个叫Starman的小人
Dialogue: 2,0:00:14.88,0:00:20.82,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Tesla roadster complete with a Starman mannequin first into orbit and then on
Dialogue: 1,0:00:20.82,0:00:24.44,720PCN,,0,0,0,,原定去火星，实际是进入了绕日椭圆轨道
Dialogue: 2,0:00:20.82,0:00:24.44,720PEN,,0,0,0,,what was meant to be a journey to Mars but now looks more like an elliptical
Dialogue: 1,0:00:24.44,0:00:28.27,720PCN,,0,0,0,,远日点达到了火星木星之间的小行星带
Dialogue: 2,0:00:24.44,0:00:28.27,720PEN,,0,0,0,,orbit extending out to the asteroid belt between Mars and Jupiter.
Dialogue: 1,0:00:28.65,0:00:33.44,720PCN,,0,0,0,,当重型猎鹰成功把载荷送进深空的时候
Dialogue: 2,0:00:28.65,0:00:33.44,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Whilst the Falcon 9 heavy proved that it could launch a payload into deep space
Dialogue: 1,0:00:33.44,0:00:38.87,720PCN,,0,0,0,,Starman和跑车的应该会很悠闲
Dialogue: 2,0:00:33.44,0:00:38.87,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Starman and the Roasters journey itself is going to be a pretty leisurely one just
Dialogue: 1,0:00:38.87,0:00:42.93,720PCN,,0,0,0,,就像我们发射进深空的所有其他东西一样，不管是假人、跑车还是
Dialogue: 2,0:00:38.87,0:00:42.93,720PEN,,0,0,0,,like everything else we've launched into deep space fine for mannequins, cars and
Dialogue: 1,0:00:42.93,0:00:48.09,720PCN,,0,0,0,,真正的探测器，但对人来说就不这样了。去火星平均要花九个月
Dialogue: 2,0:00:42.93,0:00:48.09,720PEN,,0,0,0,,robotic probes but not so good for humans. With an average time of nine
Dialogue: 1,0:00:48.09,0:00:52.46,720PCN,,0,0,0,,中间要面临辐射、失重
Dialogue: 2,0:00:48.09,0:00:52.46,720PEN,,0,0,0,,months to get to Mars the risk from radiation, weightlessness and
Dialogue: 1,0:00:52.46,0:00:57.03,720PCN,,0,0,0,,心理、精神上的问题，更不用说他们还要携带大量物资
Dialogue: 2,0:00:52.46,0:00:57.03,720PEN,,0,0,0,,psychological issues is high, not to mention with supplies they need to carry
Dialogue: 1,0:00:57.03,0:01:01.25,720PCN,,0,0,0,,就算他们能在飞船上种菜、循环用水，要带的东西也不少
Dialogue: 2,0:00:57.03,0:01:01.25,720PEN,,0,0,0,,even if they're going to grow their own food and recycle their own water.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:01.67,0:01:07.95,720PCN,,0,0,0,,但如果你能缩短旅途时间，之前提到的所有风险
Dialogue: 2,0:01:01.67,0:01:07.95,720PEN,,0,0,0,,But if you can reduce the time it takes to get there all these things become much more
Dialogue: 1,0:01:07.95,0:01:13.38,720PCN,,0,0,0,,都会变得轻松，然而人类曾经研究过二十来年的核动力火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:01:07.95,0:01:13.38,720PEN,,0,0,0,,manageable, however there is a technology using nuclear power that was developed
Dialogue: 1,0:01:13.38,0:01:19.95,720PCN,,0,0,0,,美国在上世纪五十年代到七十年代最开始搞
Dialogue: 2,0:01:13.38,0:01:19.95,720PEN,,0,0,0,,for about 20 years from the 50s to the 1970s originally by the US and the
Dialogue: 1,0:01:19.95,0:01:25.68,720PCN,,0,0,0,,后来苏联为了火星任务也在七八十年代开始研究，但后来随着
Dialogue: 2,0:01:19.95,0:01:25.68,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Soviets for Mars missions proposed in the 1970s and 80s but was shelved after
Dialogue: 1,0:01:25.68,0:01:30.60,720PCN,,0,0,0,,任务取消也跟着搁置。但现在人类又对火星感兴趣了
Dialogue: 2,0:01:25.68,0:01:30.60,720PEN,,0,0,0,,the demise of the missions themselves. Now with our revived interest in Mars
Dialogue: 1,0:01:30.60,0:01:35.49,720PCN,,0,0,0,,所以用于深空探测的核动力火箭也再次写入日程
Dialogue: 2,0:01:30.60,0:01:35.49,720PEN,,0,0,0,,missions and trips to deep space nuclear-powered rockets are back on the
Dialogue: 1,0:01:35.49,0:01:41.00,720PCN,,0,0,0,,从而减少太空旅行时间、增加运力
Dialogue: 2,0:01:35.49,0:01:41.00,720PEN,,0,0,0,,agenda as a way to cut transit time and carry greater payloads.
Dialogue: 1,0:01:41.30,0:01:48.89,720PCN,,0,0,0,,但我们得先说明，核动力火箭是只用在太空内的
Dialogue: 2,0:01:41.30,0:01:48.89,720PEN,,0,0,0,,But we have to make a distinction here the nuclear rocket engines are only for use in space
Dialogue: 1,0:01:48.89,0:01:53.57,720PCN,,0,0,0,,因为这类火箭相比于传统化学火箭推力非常小
Dialogue: 2,0:01:48.89,0:01:53.57,720PEN,,0,0,0,,because they have a much lower thrust to weight ratio compared to chemical
Dialogue: 1,0:01:53.57,0:01:58.14,720PCN,,0,0,0,,所以将仍然使用化学火箭将载荷送进地球轨道
Dialogue: 2,0:01:53.57,0:01:58.14,720PEN,,0,0,0,,rockets and so chemical ones will still be doing the heavy lifting from Earth
Dialogue: 1,0:01:58.14,0:02:04.40,720PCN,,0,0,75,,当到了太空，不需要克服地球重力了，核动力火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:01:58.14,0:02:04.40,720PEN,,0,0,55,,into orbit but once they're an away from a gravity of Earth nuclear engines can
Dialogue: 1,0:02:04.40,0:02:08.16,720PCN,,0,0,75,,就会高效得多。如今的化学火箭虽然推力大
Dialogue: 2,0:02:04.40,0:02:08.16,720PEN,,0,0,55,,be much more efficient. Now as powerful as chemical rockets are
Dialogue: 1,0:02:08.16,0:02:12.38,720PCN,,0,0,0,,但它们有个问题是除了燃料还得携带氧化剂
Dialogue: 2,0:02:08.16,0:02:12.38,720PEN,,0,0,0,,they have a problem they need to carry not only the fuel but also the oxygen
Dialogue: 1,0:02:12.38,0:02:17.10,720PCN,,0,0,0,,才能燃烧，这使得火箭多了很多重量，也减少了能带的载荷量
Dialogue: 2,0:02:12.38,0:02:17.10,720PEN,,0,0,0,,allow it to burn which makes the Rockets much heavier and also reduces the payload available.
Dialogue: 1,0:02:17.57,0:02:21.32,720PCN,,0,0,0,,第一种核动力火箭，热核火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:02:17.57,0:02:21.32,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The first type of nuclear rocket, the nuclear thermal one
Dialogue: 1,0:02:21.32,0:02:26.54,720PCN,,0,0,75,,不需要液氧就能工作
Dialogue: 2,0:02:21.32,0:02:26.54,720PEN,,0,0,55,,does away with the liquid oxygen altogether and instead passes liquid
Dialogue: 1,0:02:26.54,0:02:32.18,720PCN,,0,0,75,,它内部液氢流过核反应堆后被加热
Dialogue: 2,0:02:26.54,0:02:32.18,720PEN,,0,0,55,,hydrogen fuel through a nuclear reactor to heat it up to a superheated gas, this
Dialogue: 1,0:02:32.18,0:02:36.26,720PCN,,0,0,75,,然后这股热气从尾喷口喷出，这步和化学火箭一样
Dialogue: 2,0:02:32.18,0:02:36.26,720PEN,,0,0,55,,hot gas has been ejected from the engine in the same way as a chemical rocket and
Dialogue: 1,0:02:36.26,0:02:41.18,720PCN,,0,0,75,,于是就产生了推力。两者区别在于，化学火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:02:36.26,0:02:41.18,720PEN,,0,0,55,,that's where it creates its thrust. The difference is that when a chemical
Dialogue: 1,0:02:41.18,0:02:46.97,720PCN,,0,0,0,,发动机燃烧氢氧生成水，水很重
Dialogue: 2,0:02:41.18,0:02:46.97,720PEN,,0,0,0,,rocket engine burns hydrogen & oxygen the byproduct which is water vapour is heavy
Dialogue: 1,0:02:46.97,0:02:51.86,720PCN,,0,0,0,,在相同温度下速度就慢
Dialogue: 2,0:02:46.97,0:02:51.86,720PEN,,0,0,0,,and therefore as a given temperature its velocity is lower and therefore the
Dialogue: 1,0:02:51.86,0:02:57.26,720PCN,,0,0,0,,产生的推力就小。而核火箭不燃烧氢
Dialogue: 2,0:02:51.86,0:02:57.26,720PEN,,0,0,0,,thrust created is less. Because a nuclear thermal engine doesn't burn the hydrogen
Dialogue: 1,0:02:57.26,0:03:01.82,720PCN,,0,0,0,,它只是把氢加热，当热的氢气被排出时
Dialogue: 2,0:02:57.26,0:03:01.82,720PEN,,0,0,0,,it just heats it up it's still pure hydrogen when it leaves the rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:03:01.82,0:03:07.55,720PCN,,0,0,0,,由于氢是最轻的元素，温度相同时它排出的速度也是最快的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:01.82,0:03:07.55,720PEN,,0,0,0,,engine and as hydrogen is the lightest element its exit velocity is the highest
Dialogue: 1,0:03:07.55,0:03:11.66,720PCN,,0,0,0,,于是产生的推力也更大
Dialogue: 2,0:03:07.55,0:03:11.66,720PEN,,0,0,0,,for a given temperature and therefore the thrust is considerably more
Dialogue: 1,0:03:11.66,0:03:16.85,720PCN,,0,0,0,,火箭的燃烧效率单位是秒
Dialogue: 2,0:03:11.66,0:03:16.85,720PEN,,0,0,0,,A rockets efficiency or how well it makes use of its fuel is measured in seconds
Dialogue: 1,0:03:16.85,0:03:22.76,720PCN,,0,0,0,,物理名称叫“比冲”，意义是
Dialogue: 2,0:03:16.85,0:03:22.76,720PEN,,0,0,0,,of specific impulse sounds complicated but put simply it means how long in
Dialogue: 1,0:03:22.76,0:03:28.25,720PCN,,0,0,0,,单位质量燃料可以单位推力推动几秒
Dialogue: 2,0:03:22.76,0:03:28.25,720PEN,,0,0,0,,seconds one pound of propellant can deliver one pound of thrust
Dialogue: 1,0:03:28.47,0:03:35.09,720PCN,,0,0,0,,坠吼的化学火箭比冲可以达到450秒，而早期的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:28.47,0:03:35.09,720PEN,,0,0,0,,the best chemical rockets have a specific impulse around 450 seconds whereas the early
Dialogue: 1,0:03:35.09,0:03:41.57,720PCN,,0,0,0,,测试核火箭就拥有高达900的比冲，几乎是最强化学火箭的两倍
Dialogue: 2,0:03:35.09,0:03:41.57,720PEN,,0,0,0,,test nuclear Rockets had a specific impulse of around 900 seconds twice as efficient.
Dialogue: 1,0:03:41.72,0:03:45.89,720PCN,,0,0,0,,另外由于你不用带大量的
Dialogue: 2,0:03:41.72,0:03:45.89,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Now couple that to a fact when you don't now need to carry a lot of
Dialogue: 1,0:03:45.89,0:03:50.36,720PCN,,0,0,0,,液氧，使得你要么可以飞得更快
Dialogue: 2,0:03:45.89,0:03:50.36,720PEN,,0,0,0,,heavy liquid oxygen around with you and this means you can either go faster or
Dialogue: 1,0:03:50.36,0:03:55.43,720PCN,,0,0,0,,要么可以带更重的载荷。从五十年代中期开始就已经有这方面的理论研究
Dialogue: 2,0:03:50.36,0:03:55.43,720PEN,,0,0,0,,carry greater payloads. From the mid-1950s this principle was studied
Dialogue: 1,0:03:55.43,0:03:59.21,720PCN,,0,0,0,,新墨西哥州的洛斯阿拉莫斯原子能实验室当年就做了广泛的研究
Dialogue: 2,0:03:55.43,0:03:59.21,720PEN,,0,0,0,,extensively at the Atomic Energy Commission laboratory at Los Alamos in
Dialogue: 1,0:03:59.21,0:04:03.15,720PCN,,0,0,0,,当时的项目名称叫Rover
Dialogue: 2,0:03:59.21,0:04:03.15,720PEN,,0,0,0,,New Mexico through a program called Project Rover.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:03.32,0:04:10.19,720PCN,,0,0,0,,1959年，一个叫Kiwi的实验反应堆在内华达州的Jackass Flasts试验场准备测试
Dialogue: 2,0:04:03.32,0:04:10.19,720PEN,,0,0,0,,By 1959 an experimental reactor called Kiwi who was ready for testing in Jackass Flats in Nevada
Dialogue: 1,0:04:10.19,0:04:15.23,720PCN,,0,0,0,,最后成功达到了100兆瓦，最后在
Dialogue: 2,0:04:10.19,0:04:15.23,720PEN,,0,0,0,,and successfully ran at a power of a 100 megawatts and then up to a full
Dialogue: 1,0:04:15.23,0:04:22.04,720PCN,,0,0,0,,1962年达到了1000兆瓦的功率。后来，把Kiwi改成
Dialogue: 2,0:04:15.23,0:04:22.04,720PEN,,0,0,0,,power rating of 1000 megawatts in 1962. The program to turn Kiwi into a working
Dialogue: 1,0:04:22.04,0:04:27.44,720PCN,,0,0,0,,能用的发动机的工程全程叫“核动力发动机火箭载具应用”，缩写是NERVA
Dialogue: 2,0:04:22.04,0:04:27.44,720PEN,,0,0,0,,engine was called nuclear engines rocket vehicle applications or NERVA
Dialogue: 1,0:04:27.44,0:04:33.34,720PCN,,0,0,0,,1967年测试再次成功，NRX-A6发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:04:27.44,0:04:33.34,720PEN,,0,0,0,,again the tests were successful and in 1967 the NRX-A6
Dialogue: 1,0:04:33.34,0:04:39.31,720PCN,,0,0,0,,成功点火一小时，而且如果不是测试场地氢气有限，还能工作更久
Dialogue: 2,0:04:33.34,0:04:39.31,720PEN,,0,0,0,,engine fired successfully for an hour as the tests continued the engine
Dialogue: 1,0:04:39.31,0:04:44.25,720PCN,,0,0,0,,成功点火一小时，而且如果不是测试场地氢气有限，还能工作更久
Dialogue: 2,0:04:39.31,0:04:44.25,720PEN,,0,0,0,,runtime was only really limited by the supplies of liquid hydrogen at the test site.
Dialogue: 1,0:04:44.87,0:04:49.38,720PCN,,0,0,0,,虽然发动机测试结果说明这个概念OK，但其他方面还有问题
Dialogue: 2,0:04:44.87,0:04:49.38,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Whilst these test engines proved the concept there were still issues the
Dialogue: 1,0:04:49.38,0:04:53.02,720PCN,,0,0,0,,保护飞行乘组、飞控设备不受辐射的保护罩的重量太大
Dialogue: 2,0:04:49.38,0:04:53.02,720PEN,,0,0,0,,weight of the shielding to protect for crew and the control electronics from
Dialogue: 1,0:04:53.02,0:04:57.66,720PCN,,0,0,0,,使得引擎重量过大，还有个问题是
Dialogue: 2,0:04:53.02,0:04:57.66,720PEN,,0,0,0,,the radiation made the engines very heavy, there was also the problem of what
Dialogue: 1,0:04:57.66,0:05:03.15,720PCN,,0,0,0,,如果核动力火箭在发射台上出问题
Dialogue: 2,0:04:57.66,0:05:03.15,720PEN,,0,0,0,,would happen if a nuclear engine rocket were to fail on a launch pad or were to
Dialogue: 1,0:05:03.15,0:05:07.90,720PCN,,0,0,0,,或者从轨道失控再入的时候，放射性物质一旦落到
Dialogue: 2,0:05:03.15,0:05:07.90,720PEN,,0,0,0,,fall back to earth from orbit and spread highly radioactive material over
Dialogue: 1,0:05:07.90,0:05:12.72,720PCN,,0,0,0,,有人的地方后果很严重。同时它还有过热的问题
Dialogue: 2,0:05:07.90,0:05:12.72,720PEN,,0,0,0,,potentially highly populated areas. And there was also issues with overheating
Dialogue: 1,0:05:12.72,0:05:18.72,720PCN,,0,0,0,,燃料本来可以作为冷却剂的，但如果燃料用完后发动机没关好怎么办
Dialogue: 2,0:05:12.72,0:05:18.72,720PEN,,0,0,0,,if the fuel which acted as a coolant ran out before the engine was shut down properly.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:19.12,0:05:23.19,720PCN,,0,0,0,,但经过几年的测试，这些发动机都已经准备好进太空
Dialogue: 2,0:05:19.12,0:05:23.19,720PEN,,0,0,0,,But after years of testing they were deemed ready for use in space and
Dialogue: 1,0:05:23.19,0:05:27.62,720PCN,,0,0,0,,NRX发动机都打算在70年代上太空了
Dialogue: 2,0:05:23.19,0:05:27.62,720PEN,,0,0,0,,NRX seemed to be on track to make it there by the late 1970s.
Dialogue: 1,0:05:28.63,0:05:32.97,720PCN,,0,0,0,,在铁幕另一边，苏联首席火箭工程师科罗廖夫
Dialogue: 2,0:05:28.63,0:05:32.97,720PEN,,0,0,0,,On the other side of the Iron Curtain the Soviet chief rocket designer Sergey Korolyov
Dialogue: 1,0:05:32.97,0:05:39.00,720PCN,,0,0,0,,也打算让他的N1超级烟花带着核动力上面级
Dialogue: 2,0:05:32.97,0:05:39.00,720PEN,,0,0,0,,expected his N1 super heavy lift rocket to carry a nuclear upper stage,
Dialogue: 1,0:05:39.61,0:05:45.25,720PCN,,0,0,0,,从而让他的火箭拥有星际航行能力。他的团队考虑了几种方案
Dialogue: 2,0:05:39.61,0:05:45.25,720PEN,,0,0,0,,giving the vehicle a formidable interplanetary capability. His team considered several options
Dialogue: 1,0:05:45.25,0:05:48.42,720PCN,,0,0,0,,要么在三级火箭上放两个核动力级
Dialogue: 2,0:05:45.25,0:05:48.42,720PEN,,0,0,0,,either two nuclear other stages on a three-stage rocket
Dialogue: 1,0:05:48.75,0:05:54.96,720PCN,,0,0,0,,或者在二级或者三级火箭上放一个核动力级，无论哪种构型
Dialogue: 2,0:05:48.75,0:05:54.96,720PEN,,0,0,0,,or a single nuclear stage on a two or three stage rocket. With any of these options the N1
Dialogue: 1,0:05:54.96,0:05:59.13,720PCN,,0,0,0,,N1火箭的上面级都要捆一堆核动力火箭
Dialogue: 2,0:05:54.96,0:05:59.13,720PEN,,0,0,0,,upper stages would have had to cluster large numbers of nuclear engines
Dialogue: 1,0:05:59.13,0:06:04.71,720PCN,,0,0,0,,比美国的设计方案多多了。但热核火箭上面级
Dialogue: 2,0:05:59.13,0:06:04.71,720PEN,,0,0,0,,together many more than on the American designs. But a nuclear thermal upper
Dialogue: 1,0:06:04.71,0:06:11.12,720PCN,,0,0,75,,去火星的载荷量的计算理论值仍然比传统化学火箭多50%
Dialogue: 2,0:06:04.71,0:06:11.12,720PEN,,0,0,55,,stage was calculated to be able to deliver up to 50% more payload to Mars than a chemical one.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:11.22,0:06:15.62,720PCN,,0,0,0,,同时，热核火箭也并不是唯一的选择
Dialogue: 2,0:06:11.22,0:06:15.62,720PEN,,0,0,0,,However the nuclear thermal engines weren't the only options available on the table.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:15.77,0:06:19.40,720PCN,,0,0,75,,科罗廖夫其实青睐于另一种核能方式
Dialogue: 2,0:06:15.77,0:06:19.40,720PEN,,0,0,55,,Korolev favored another way of harnessing atomic power,
Dialogue: 1,0:06:19.52,0:06:26.70,720PCN,,0,0,75,,把核反应堆与电推引擎结合在一起，推力更小
Dialogue: 2,0:06:19.52,0:06:26.70,720PEN,,0,0,55,,pairing a nuclear reactor with an electric ion engine although the system provided much less thrust.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:27.05,0:06:29.83,720PCN,,0,0,0,,但相比于热核火箭，这种方法长时间提供小推力更有效率
Dialogue: 2,0:06:27.05,0:06:29.83,720PEN,,0,0,0,,It was even more efficient and would provide a low
Dialogue: 1,0:06:29.83,0:06:35.65,720PCN,,0,0,0,,但相比于热核火箭，这种方法长时间提供小推力更有效率
Dialogue: 2,0:06:29.83,0:06:35.65,720PEN,,0,0,0,,thrust for a very long period of time compared to the quick bursts like the nuclear thermal ones.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:36.02,0:06:38.65,720PCN,,0,0,0,,最近几年由于太阳帆板技术的进步
Dialogue: 2,0:06:36.02,0:06:38.65,720PEN,,0,0,0,,In recent times advances in solar panel
Dialogue: 1,0:06:38.65,0:06:44.44,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这类核反应堆+电推的设计就略显多余了
Dialogue: 2,0:06:38.65,0:06:44.44,720PEN,,0,0,0,,design has made nuclear reactor powered iron engines much less likely but for
Dialogue: 1,0:06:44.44,0:06:49.03,720PCN,,0,0,0,,但对于土星以外的深空任务，没有足够的太阳辐射
Dialogue: 2,0:06:44.44,0:06:49.03,720PEN,,0,0,0,,deep space missions beyond Saturn where there is not enough sunlight to operate
Dialogue: 1,0:06:49.03,0:06:54.87,720PCN,,0,0,0,,核动力火箭则又变成唯一的选择
Dialogue: 2,0:06:49.03,0:06:54.87,720PEN,,0,0,0,,solar panels successfully nuclear power becomes pretty much the only option.
Dialogue: 1,0:06:54.87,0:07:00.90,720PCN,,0,0,0,,计算显示相比传统化学火箭，电推能提升70%的运力
Dialogue: 2,0:06:54.87,0:07:00.90,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Calculations showed that ion drives will be able to transport 70% more payload
Dialogue: 1,0:07:00.90,0:07:03.52,720PCN,,0,0,0,,计算显示相比传统化学火箭，电推能提升70%的运力
Dialogue: 2,0:07:00.90,0:07:03.52,720PEN,,0,0,0,,than chemical engines on a mission to Mars.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:04.02,0:07:07.77,720PCN,,0,0,0,,N1项目差不多嗝屁了以后
Dialogue: 2,0:07:04.02,0:07:07.77,720PEN,,0,0,0,,After the N1 rocket quite literally fell by the wayside
Dialogue: 1,0:07:07.77,0:07:11.08,720PCN,,0,0,75,,苏联火星任务的大旗就交到了切洛梅手里
Dialogue: 2,0:07:07.77,0:07:11.08,720PEN,,0,0,55,,the chief designer Vladimir Chelomei was in pole position
Dialogue: 1,0:07:11.08,0:07:15.06,720PCN,,0,0,75,,苏联火星任务的大旗就交到了切洛梅手里
Dialogue: 2,0:07:11.08,0:07:15.06,720PEN,,0,0,55,,to design a rocket for the Soviet manned Mars mission.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:15.06,0:07:23.30,720PCN,,0,0,0,,MK700上面级将用UR700火箭多次发射，然后在轨组装
Dialogue: 2,0:07:15.06,0:07:23.30,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The enormous MK 700 was to be assembled in orbit with multiple launches for the modular UR700 rocket.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:23.42,0:07:27.46,720PCN,,0,0,0,,MK700上面级将靠其VG设计局的RD-0410热核火箭发动机实现星际航行
Dialogue: 2,0:07:23.42,0:07:27.46,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The MK 700 would make its interplanetary burn with a
Dialogue: 1,0:07:27.46,0:07:34.57,720PCN,,0,0,0,,MK700上面级将靠其VG设计局的RD-0410热核火箭发动机实现星际航行
Dialogue: 2,0:07:27.46,0:07:34.57,720PEN,,0,0,0,,nuclear thermal engine built by Valentin Glushko's design bureau and called the RD-0410.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:35.12,0:07:38.77,720PCN,,0,0,0,,发动机在哈萨克斯坦东部进行了测试，达到了910秒的比冲
Dialogue: 2,0:07:35.12,0:07:38.77,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The engine made it as far as testing at the test site in north
Dialogue: 1,0:07:38.77,0:07:43.84,720PCN,,0,0,0,,发动机在哈萨克斯坦东部进行了测试，达到了910秒的比冲
Dialogue: 2,0:07:38.77,0:07:43.84,720PEN,,0,0,0,,east kazakhstan demonstrating yet again Glushko's mastery of rocket engine
Dialogue: 1,0:07:43.84,0:07:50.85,720PCN,,0,0,0,,发动机在哈萨克斯坦东部进行了测试，达到了910秒的比冲
Dialogue: 2,0:07:43.84,0:07:50.85,720PEN,,0,0,0,,efficiency the RD-0410 showed a capability of 910 seconds of specific impulse.
Dialogue: 1,0:07:51.20,0:07:54.40,720PCN,,0,0,0,,然而到了1972年，公众与政府
Dialogue: 2,0:07:51.20,0:07:54.40,720PEN,,0,0,0,,However by 1972 and due to the loss of
Dialogue: 1,0:07:54.40,0:07:58.96,720PCN,,0,0,0,,逐渐对太空失去兴趣，NASA研发
Dialogue: 2,0:07:54.40,0:07:58.96,720PEN,,0,0,0,,interest in space by the public and the government in the US funding for
Dialogue: 1,0:07:58.96,0:08:02.80,720PCN,,0,0,0,,火星任务与NERVA引擎的资金也被国会撤回
Dialogue: 2,0:07:58.96,0:08:02.80,720PEN,,0,0,0,,NASA's mars mission and NERVA was cancelled by congress.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:03.22,0:08:08.82,720PCN,,0,0,0,,后来航天飞机把目标聚焦在近地空间，核动力火箭更是没有了用武之地
Dialogue: 2,0:08:03.22,0:08:08.82,720PEN,,0,0,0,,As the space shuttle returned to focus to low-earth orbit where nuclear engines weren't required
Dialogue: 1,0:08:09.07,0:08:12.40,720PCN,,0,0,0,,苏联那边也转而研发暴风雪号来与美国抗衡
Dialogue: 2,0:08:09.07,0:08:12.40,720PEN,,0,0,0,,and the soviet priority was to match this capability,
Dialogue: 1,0:08:12.47,0:08:16.25,720PCN,,0,0,0,,使得他们研发核动力飞船的计划也取消了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:12.47,0:08:16.25,720PEN,,0,0,0,,their research into nuclear-powered spacecraft also stalled.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:16.47,0:08:23.71,720PCN,,0,0,0,,然而这些事在里根总统80年代末提出星球大战计划的时候又被翻出来了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:16.47,0:08:23.71,720PEN,,0,0,0,,However things picked up again with President Ronald Reagan's Star Wars initiative in the late 1980s project
Dialogue: 1,0:08:23.71,0:08:28.93,720PCN,,0,0,75,,利用球床反应堆设计的Timberwind发动机
Dialogue: 2,0:08:23.71,0:08:28.93,720PEN,,0,0,55,,Timberwind advanced the engines using a pebble bed reactor design and increased
Dialogue: 1,0:08:28.93,0:08:34.20,720PCN,,0,0,75,,达到了接近1000秒的比冲，而这个项目也直接引领了
Dialogue: 2,0:08:28.93,0:08:34.20,720PEN,,0,0,55,,the specific impulse to nearly 1,000 seconds it also led to the development
Dialogue: 1,0:08:34.20,0:08:39.72,720PCN,,0,0,75,,后来现代的碳基复合材料的研发，但它仍然遇到了一些技术问题
Dialogue: 2,0:08:34.20,0:08:39.72,720PEN,,0,0,55,,of modern carbon composite materials but it also faced technical issues which
Dialogue: 1,0:08:39.72,0:08:46.40,720PCN,,0,0,75,,使它很难用于太空，最终也惨遭撤资
Dialogue: 2,0:08:39.72,0:08:46.40,720PEN,,0,0,55,,would have made it very difficult to use as a space based engine system and funding was eventually dropped.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:46.40,0:08:52.52,720PCN,,0,0,0,,最近，毛子国家原子能中心的工程师正在研发
Dialogue: 2,0:08:46.40,0:08:52.52,720PEN,,0,0,0,,More recently Russian engineers at the State Energy Corporation ROSATOM are working on a
Dialogue: 1,0:08:52.52,0:08:56.20,720PCN,,0,0,0,,一种新的核电推进系统“TEM”
Dialogue: 2,0:08:52.52,0:08:56.20,720PEN,,0,0,0,,form of nuclear electric propulsion called 'TEM'.
Dialogue: 1,0:08:56.62,0:09:04.17,720PCN,,0,0,0,,缩写全称是"运输能量模块"，反应堆是双模式工作的
Dialogue: 2,0:08:56.62,0:09:04.17,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The acronym translates to transport an energy unit the name indicates a nuclear reactor capable of
Dialogue: 1,0:09:04.17,0:09:09.57,720PCN,,0,0,0,,当发动机不工作时，它能切换为
Dialogue: 2,0:09:04.17,0:09:09.57,720PEN,,0,0,0,,bimodal operation that is when it's not powering engines it can be switched to a
Dialogue: 1,0:09:09.57,0:09:14.00,720PCN,,0,0,0,,低功率模式，为飞船居住舱等其他系统供电
Dialogue: 2,0:09:09.57,0:09:14.00,720PEN,,0,0,0,,low power mode to power the living quarters and other onboard systems.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:14.37,0:09:19.08,720PCN,,0,0,0,,根据TEM的设计者说，TEM打算今年进行一次地面测试
Dialogue: 2,0:09:14.37,0:09:19.08,720PEN,,0,0,0,,According to the designers TEM has a goal of testing a ground-based engine
Dialogue: 1,0:09:19.08,0:09:25.02,720PCN,,0,0,0,,并于2025年发射一个发动机原型，如果不被撤资的话
Dialogue: 2,0:09:19.08,0:09:25.02,720PEN,,0,0,0,,this year and launching a prototype by 2025 if funding can be secured.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:25.68,0:09:32.15,720PCN,,0,0,0,,这项技术理论上能让地火旅行时间缩短到45天
Dialogue: 2,0:09:25.68,0:09:32.15,720PEN,,0,0,0,,The technology could in theory enable a journey from Earth to Mars in just 45 days.
Dialogue: 1,0:09:32.45,0:09:36.72,720PCN,,0,0,0,,NASA也在进行新的研究
Dialogue: 2,0:09:32.45,0:09:36.72,720PEN,,0,0,0,,NASA is also conducting new research into rapid transit technologies
Dialogue: 1,0:09:36.72,0:09:40.85,720PCN,,0,0,0,,来缓解人类长期在星际环境下受到的影响
Dialogue: 2,0:09:36.72,0:09:40.85,720PEN,,0,0,0,,to mitigate the long-term effects of interplanetary space on the human body
Dialogue: 1,0:09:41.57,0:09:46.41,720PCN,,0,0,0,,与毛子一样，NASA也把热核火箭作为一种解决方案
Dialogue: 2,0:09:41.57,0:09:46.41,720PEN,,0,0,0,,Like Russia, NASA sees nuclear thermal propulsion as a solution here the goal
Dialogue: 1,0:09:46.41,0:09:51.48,720PCN,,0,0,0,,当前研究的目标是降低成本，同时降低核燃料的风险
Dialogue: 2,0:09:46.41,0:09:51.48,720PEN,,0,0,0,,of the current research is to reduce for cost and risk of the nuclear fuel by
Dialogue: 1,0:09:51.48,0:09:56.73,720PCN,,0,0,0,,方法是研发一种低浓铀燃料
Dialogue: 2,0:09:51.48,0:09:56.73,720PEN,,0,0,0,,developing a suitable form of low enriched uranium with a concentration of
Dialogue: 1,0:09:56.73,0:10:01.47,720PCN,,0,0,0,,铀-235含量只有3-4%，相比于早期版本使用的武器级的90%
Dialogue: 2,0:09:56.73,0:10:01.47,720PEN,,0,0,0,,3-4% uranium-235 compared to a 90% concentration
Dialogue: 1,0:10:01.47,0:10:04.62,720PCN,,0,0,0,,铀-235含量只有3-4%，相比于早期版本使用的武器级的90%
Dialogue: 2,0:10:01.47,0:10:04.62,720PEN,,0,0,0,,of weapons-grade fuel in the earlier designs.
